04071nam a22006495i 9780520383982DE-B159720220424125308.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220424t20212021cau    fo  d z      eng d  a2020047428  a9780520383982  a(DE-B1597)577690  a(OCoLC)1285508029  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA00aTR642b.A435 2021 4aTR642b.A435 2021eb 7aPHO0100002bisacsh04a7702231 aAlbers, Kate Palmer, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Night Albums :bVisibility and the Ephemeral Photograph /cKate Palmer Albers. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (168 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- tI Ephemerality, over Time -- tII Ways of Seeing and “Live” Photography -- tIII Future Visibility -- tIV Revised Foundations -- tCoda -- tAcknowledgments -- tNotes -- tList of Illustrations -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWe live in an era of abundant photography. It may then seem counterintuitive to study photographs that disappear or are difficult to discern, but Kate Palmer Albers argues that it is precisely this current cultural moment that allows us to recognize what has always been a basic and foundational, yet unseen, condition of photography: its ephemerality. Through a series of case studies spanning the history of photography, The Night Albums takes up the provocations of artists who collectively redefine how we experience visibility. From the protracted hesitancies of photography's origins, to conceptual and performative art that has emerged since the 1960s, and to the waves of technological experimentation flourishing today, Albers foregrounds artists who offer fleeting, hidden, conditional, and future modes of visibility. By unveiling how ephemerality shapes the photographic experience, she ultimately proposes an expanded framework for the medium.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEphemeral art. 0aPhotographyxPhilosophy. 0aPhotography, ArtisticvCase studies. 0aPhotography, ArtisticxHistory. 7aPhotography / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2021z9783110753790oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishz978311075403208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052038398240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520383982423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520383982/original  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075403-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DPKb2021